          <li><a href="https://psycnet.apa.org/record/2015-49040-001" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Kushlev &amp; Dunn (2015) — Checking Email Less Frequently Reduces Stress (Computers in Human Behavior)</a> — Research showing that reduced checking frequency — not reduced total use — produces lower stress and higher productivity.</li>
